      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Impact of Right-Sizing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Workload: 50,000 requests/day\n# Mix after right-sizing: 60% Haiku, 30% Sonnet, 10% Opus\n# Average: 800 input tokens, 200 output tokens per request\n\nDAILY_REQUESTS = 50_000\nMIX = {\"claude-haiku-4-5\": 0.60, \"claude-sonnet-4-6\": 0.30, \"claude-opus-4-8\": 0.10}\nAVG_IN, AVG_OUT = 800, 200\n\n# Prices per 1M (approximate)\nPRICES = {\n    \"claude-haiku-4-5\":  {\"i\": 0.80, \"o\": 4.00},\n    \"claude-sonnet-4-6\": {\"i\": 3.00, \"o\": 15.00},\n    \"claude-opus-4-8\":   {\"i\": 15.00,\"o\": 75.00},\n}\n\ndef daily_cost(mix: dict) -> float:\n    total = 0.0\n    for model, fraction in mix.items():\n        n = DAILY_REQUESTS * fraction\n        r = PRICES[model]\n        total += n * (AVG_IN * r[\"i\"] + AVG_OUT * r[\"o\"]) / 1_000_000\n    return total\n\nall_sonnet = {\"claude-haiku-4-5\": 0, \"claude-sonnet-4-6\": 1.0, \"claude-opus-4-8\": 0}\nall_opus   = {\"claude-haiku-4-5\": 0, \"claude-sonnet-4-6\": 0,   \"claude-opus-4-8\": 1.0}\n\nprint(f\"All Sonnet:  ${daily_cost(all_sonnet):.2f}/day   (${daily_cost(all_sonnet)*30:.0f}/mo)\")\nprint(f\"Mixed:       ${daily_cost(MIX):.2f}/day   (${daily_cost(MIX)*30:.0f}/mo)\")\nprint(f\"All Opus:    ${daily_cost(all_opus):.2f}/day   (${daily_cost(all_opus)*30:.0f}/mo)\")\n# All Sonnet:  $210/day   ($6,300/mo)\n# Mixed:       $93/day    ($2,790/mo)   \u2190 56% reduction vs all-Sonnet\n# All Opus:    $1,050/day ($31,500/mo)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building a Router"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once you have a quality profile per tier per task type, encode the routing logic explicitly. The router itself should be cheap to run \u2014 use Haiku or a local classifier:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\nimport json\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef route_request(user_message: str, context: dict = {}) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the appropriate model ID for this request.\"\"\"\n\n    # Cheap Haiku call to classify complexity\n    routing_resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        max_tokens=32,\n        messages=[\n            {\n                \"role\": \"user\",\n                \"content\": (\n                    f\"Classify this task. Reply with JSON only: \"\n                    f'{{\"tier\": \"haiku\"|\"sonnet\"|\"opus\", \"reason\": \"one word\"}}\\n\\n'\n                    f\"Task: {user_message[:500]}\"\n                ),\n            }\n        ],\n    )\n    try:\n        decision = json.loads(routing_resp.content[0].text)\n        tier = decision.get(\"tier\", \"sonnet\")\n    except Exception:\n        tier = \"sonnet\"  # safe default\n\n    return {\n        \"haiku\":  \"claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"sonnet\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        \"opus\":   \"claude-opus-4-8\",\n    }.get(tier, \"claude-sonnet-4-6\")\n\n\ndef smart_complete(user_message: str) -> str:\n    model = route_request(user_message)\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message}],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text\n"
          }
        ]
